OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FPopulation-wide "adverse health
OL,12,Feffects" will be experienced and
OL,13,Fsubstantial changes to working
OL,14,Fpractices and daily routines will be
OL,15,Frequired, forecasters said.
OL,17,FThere is likely to be significant
OL,18,Fdisruption to travel, and energy
OL,19,Fsupplies, such as water, electricity,
OL,20,Fgas or mobile phone services, could
OL,21,Falso be impacted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,FPeople are strongly recommended to
OL,7,Fkeep out of the sun, drink plenty of
OL,8,Ffluids and avoid exercising between
OL,9,F11am and 3pm when the sun is the
OL,10,Fstrongest.
OL,12,FThe Met Office has also warned people
OL,13,Fto take care when heading to coastal
OL,14,Fareas, lakes and rivers after multiple
OL,15,Fpeople died in water-related incidents
OL,16,Fduring the last heatwave at the start
OL,17,Fof the month.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,FForecasters had already warned that
OL,7,Ftemperatures are expected to hit 35C
OL,8,Fin London and 34C in Coventry on
OL,9,FTuesday, with most of southern England
OL,10,Fpredicted to be above 30C.
OL,12,FThe amber warning lasts from Monday to
OL,13,FThursday evening, and covers most of
OL,14,Fsouthern England and Wales.
OL,16,FHow to stay safe in extreme heat
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
