FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,FThe area reaches up to Lincoln and
OL,7,FStoke-on-Trent in the north for the
OL,8,Ffirst two days, and Preston, Leeds,
OL,9,FLiverpool and Bangor on Wednesday and
OL,10,FThursday.
OL,12,F"The forecast heatwave is developing
OL,13,Finto an impactful severe weather
OL,14,Fevent, with record-breaking June
OL,15,Ftemperatures and very high humidity,"
OL,16,Fsaid the Met Office's deputy chief
OL,17,Fforecaster Tom Crabtree.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,F"The combination of heat and humidity
OL,7,Fwill be oppressive and bring impacts
OL,8,Facross society from public health and
OL,9,Finfrastructure, to power and water
OL,10,Fsupplies.
OL,12,F"As well as very high daytime
OL,13,Ftemperatures, there will be
OL,14,Fconsecutive nights where temperatures
OL,15,Fdo not drop below 20C, which is called
OL,16,Fa Tropical Night.
OL,18,F"This will make it very hard for
OL,19,Fpeople to recover from the daytime
OL,20,Fheat, exacerbating the heat stress
OL,21,Fimpacts."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,FThe Met Office issued its first ever
OL,7,Fred warning for heat in July 2022,
OL,8,Fwhen 40C temperatures were expected in
OL,9,FEngland.
OL,11,FThe Royal National Lifeboat
OL,12,FAssociation (RNLA) has urged people to
OL,13,Fremember that bodies of water will
OL,14,Fstill cold despite the high
OL,15,Ftemperatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782195489
OL,3,CMet Office issues red warning for
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave of up to 40C
OL,6,F"Entering it unexpectedly can lead to
OL,7,Fcold water shock, causing a sudden
OL,8,Fincrease in breathing and heart rate,
OL,9,Fwhich may trigger panic," said
OL,10,FSamantha Hughes, the RNLA's national
OL,11,Fwater safety partner.
OL,13,F"If you find yourself struggling in
OL,14,Fthe water, remember to Float to Live:
OL,15,Ftilt your head back so your ears are
OL,16,Fsubmerged, relax and control your
OL,17,Fbreathing.
OL,26,@uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
